        <body>       
                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>Jan 27&#44; 5650<lb/></p>
            <p>Dear Dr&#33;<lb/></p>
            <p>The two letters which<lb/> you recently sent me I received&#44;<lb/> but was unable to answer before<lb/> now.  The first arrived during<lb/> my week of mourning when&#44; of<lb/> course&#44; it was impossible for me<lb/> to respond and since rising from<lb/> the &#91;Hebrew&#93; I have not had a leisure<lb/> moment until this morning.<lb/></p>
            <p>Accept my sincere thanks for your<lb/> kind words of condolence which were<lb/> very grateful indeed to me in my<lb/> affliction.  The demise of my<lb/> poor sister was indeed a sad blow<lb/> to us all especially to my parents<lb/> who in their age see their daughter<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>taken away and for her five orphaned<lb/> children who lose their mother.<lb/>  The Seminary has been consid&#45;<lb/>&#45;erably demoralized during<lb/> this month both by this inter&#45;<lb/>&#45;ruption and by the &#34;grip&#34; but<lb/> I shall try to make up again<lb/> by redoubled activity.<lb/></p>
            <p>In regard to Mr Guggenheimer<lb/> I would say that I should be<lb/> only too glad to call on him<lb/> if you would please send me<lb/> a few lines of introduction and<lb/> also inform me of his address<lb/> as I do not know where he<lb/> resides.  The attendance at the<lb/> Seminary has picked up again<lb/> and is now at its normal figure.<lb/>  Mr Sulzberger is still absent<lb/> in Europe and no one knows<lb/> his plans about returning.<lb/>  I believe that our Trustees at a<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="3"/>
            <p>recent meeting contributed a<lb/> few hundred dollars to the funds<lb/> of the Seminary.<lb/></p>
            <p>I have not seen the Israelite and<lb/> do not know what controversy<lb/> you refer to.  I am convinced<lb/> that by energy the Seminary<lb/> could be made to prosper as you<lb/> in Philadelphia have shown but<lb/> here every thing goes so slowly.<lb/>  I remain<lb/> yours faithfully<lb/> Bernard Drachman<lb/></p>
            </body>
    </text>
